<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3560</anchor> <rss>erct-002C.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002C</addr>  <route>erct-002C.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>From <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverses</link> to coherent <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" title="Inverse">inverses</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002C.agda" type="external">erct-002C.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> have a quasi-inverse <tex>g \colon  B \to  A</tex> with incoherent counit <tex>\epsilon \colon  f \circ  g \sim   1_{ B }</tex> and unit <tex>\eta \colon  g \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</tex>. We can <em>correct</em> the counit to obtain a coherent <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" title="Inverse">inverse</link> to <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 <p>The corrected counit <tex>\epsilon '  \colon  g \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</tex> is defined like so:</p>
 <tex display="block">
   \epsilon ' x : \equiv 
   \epsilon \mathopen {} \left ( f \mathopen {} \left ( f ^{-1}  x \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {} ^{-1}   \cdot   \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \mathopen {} \left ( \eta \mathopen {} \left ( f ^{-1}  x \right ) \mathclose {} \right ) \mathclose {}   \cdot   \epsilon  x
 </tex>

 <p>The coherence <tex>\chi \colon   \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon ' \circ  f</tex> can be constructed using the <link href="erct-001V.xml" type="local" title="Naturality of homotopies">naturality of homotopies</link> and the <link href="erct-001W.xml" type="local" title="Coherence for homotopies onto the identity">coherence of homotopies onto the identity</link>.</p>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3561</anchor> <rss>erct-003A.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>erct-003A</addr>  <route>erct-003A.xml</route> <date><year>2024</year> <month>1</month> <day>2</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Relating different kinds of equivalence</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>2</crumb></trail> <anchor>3562</anchor> <rss>erct-002D.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002D</addr>  <route>erct-002D.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>From <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinverses</link> to <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverses</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002D.agda" type="external">erct-002D.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> with <tex>s,r \colon  B \to  A</tex> and <tex>h_s \colon  f  \circ  s  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> and <tex>h_r \colon  r \circ  f =  1_{ A }</tex>. Then we may define a homotopy <tex>h'  \colon  s \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A }</tex> exhibiting <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex> as a retraction of <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex>. Therefore, we may define a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> to <tex>f</tex> tracked by <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 <p>We have <tex>s \circ  f  \sim  r \circ  f  \circ  s \circ  f</tex> by <tex>h_r</tex> and <tex>r \circ  f  \circ  s \circ  f \sim  r  \circ  f</tex> by <tex>h_s</tex> and <tex>r \circ  f  \sim   1_{ A }</tex> by <tex>h_r</tex>.</p>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>3</crumb></trail> <anchor>3563</anchor> <rss>erct-002E.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002E</addr>  <route>erct-002E.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" title="Inverse">Invertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" title="Inverse">invertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 <p>Let <tex>\epsilon   \colon  f \circ  f ^{-1}  =  1_{ B }</tex> be the counit of the <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" title="Inverse">inverse</link> to <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex>. Given <tex>b:B</tex>, we must show that the fiber of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>; the centre of contraction is given by the pair <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( f ^{-1}  x,  \epsilon  x \right ) \mathclose {}</tex>, and the required paths can be constructed via the <link href="erct-001R.xml" type="local" title="The univalence principle for fibers">univalence principle for fibers</link> using the unit <tex>\eta \colon  f ^{-1} \circ  f =  1_{ A }</tex>, the coherence <tex>\chi \colon   \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \circ \eta \sim \epsilon \circ  f</tex>, and the <link href="erct-001V.xml" type="local" title="Naturality of homotopies">naturality of homotopies</link>.</p>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>4</crumb></trail> <anchor>3564</anchor> <rss>erct-002F.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002F</addr>  <route>erct-002F.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">Contractible maps</link> are <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002F.agda" type="external">erct-002F.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 <p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>; we define a retraction <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex> to take <tex>b:B</tex> to the first component of the centre of contraction of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex>. To construct <tex>h_r \colon  r \circ  f \sim   1_{ A }</tex> exhibiting <tex>r</tex> as a retraction of <tex>f</tex>, we use the identification between any two elements of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>fx</tex>.</p>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>5</crumb></trail> <anchor>3565</anchor> <rss>erct-002G.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002G</addr>  <route>erct-002G.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">Contractible maps</link> are <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002G.agda" type="external">erct-002G.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 <p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>; we define a section <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex> to take <tex>b:B</tex> to the first component of the centre of contraction of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex>. The witness <tex>h_s \colon  f \circ  s \sim   1_{ B }</tex> exhibiting <tex>s</tex> as a section of <tex>f</tex>, we use the second component of the centre of contraction.</p>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>6</crumb></trail> <anchor>3566</anchor> <rss>erct-002H.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002H</addr>  <route>erct-002H.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">Contractible maps</link> are <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002H.agda" type="external">erct-002H.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 Because <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible maps</link> are both <link href="erct-002F.xml" type="local" title="Contractible maps are sections">sections</link> and <link href="erct-002G.xml" type="local" title="Contractible maps are retractions">retractions</link>.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>7</crumb></trail> <anchor>3567</anchor> <rss>erct-002M.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002M</addr>  <route>erct-002M.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">Quasi-invertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002M.agda" type="external">erct-002M.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> <link href="erct-002C.xml" type="local" title="From quasi-inverses to coherent inverses">can be improved</link> to a <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" title="Inverse">coherent inverse</link>, and <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" title="Inverse">any coherently invertible map</link> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>8</crumb></trail> <anchor>3568</anchor> <rss>erct-002N.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002N</addr>  <route>erct-002N.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002N.agda" type="external">erct-002N.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">biinvertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 As <link href="erct-002D.xml" type="local" title="From biinverses to quasi-inverses">biinvertible maps are quasi-invertible</link> and <link href="erct-002M.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-invertible maps are contractible">quasi-invertible maps are contractible</link>.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>9</crumb></trail> <anchor>3569</anchor> <rss>erct-002O.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002O</addr>  <route>erct-002O.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Pushforward along <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002O.agda" type="external">erct-002O.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>; then for any type <tex>C</tex>, the postcomposition map <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( f \circ  - \right ) \mathclose {} \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( C \to  A \right ) \mathclose {} \to   \mathopen {} \left ( C \to  B \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 <p>The <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section and retraction</link> are built using by postcomposing with the designated <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section and retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>; the witnesses for the postcomposition <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections and retractions</link> are constructed using the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for function spaces</link>.</p>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>10</crumb></trail> <anchor>3570</anchor> <rss>erct-002P.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002P</addr>  <route>erct-002P.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Restriction along <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> maps</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002P.agda" type="external">erct-002P.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> be <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>; then for any type <tex>C</tex>, the precomposition map <tex>\mathopen {} \left ( - \circ  f \right ) \mathclose {} \colon   \mathopen {} \left ( B \to  C \right ) \mathclose {} \to \mathopen {} \left ( A \to  C \right ) \mathclose {}</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> Analogous to the corresponding result for <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">pushforward along biinvertible maps</link>.</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>11</crumb></trail> <anchor>3571</anchor> <rss>erct-002Q.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002Q</addr>  <route>erct-002Q.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">Sections</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> are unique</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Q.agda" type="external">erct-002Q.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> of some <tex>r \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 <p>Using the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for dependent function spaces</link>, we can see that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> of <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex>, using the <link href="erct-0023.xml" type="local" title="The univalence principle for sections">univalence principle for sections</link>.</p>

 <p>To show that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">sections</link> of <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" title="Propositions">proposition</link>, we may assume beforehand that we have such a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>; therefore, because we have assumed a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex> already, we know that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> and <link href="erct-002N.xml" type="local" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible">therefore</link> that <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>. Because <link href="erct-0026.xml" type="local" title="Propositions are closed under retracts">propositions are closed under retracts</link>, it suffices to show that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f \circ  -</tex> at <tex>1_{ B }</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" title="Propositions">proposition</link>, which <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" title="Contractible types are propositions">follows</link> because <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>12</crumb></trail> <anchor>3572</anchor> <rss>erct-002R.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002R</addr>  <route>erct-002R.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">Retractions</link> of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link> are unique</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002R.agda" type="external">erct-002R.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> be a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> of some <tex>s \colon  B \to  A</tex>; the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> is, then, a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 Analogous to the <link href="erct-002Q.xml" type="local" title="Sections of sections are unique">corresponding result for sections of sections</link>, using the fact that the type of <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retractions</link> of <tex>f</tex> can be seen to be a <link href="erct-0025.xml" type="local" title="Retract">retract</link> of the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>- \circ  f</tex> at <tex>1_{ A }</tex>.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>13</crumb></trail> <anchor>3573</anchor> <rss>erct-002S.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002S</addr>  <route>erct-002S.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">Biinverses</link> are unique</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002S.agda" type="external">erct-002S.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>The type of <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinverses</link> of a given function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" title="Propositions">proposition</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 <link href="erct-002Q.xml" type="local" title="Sections of sections are unique">Sections of sections</link> and <link href="erct-002R.xml" type="local" title="Retractions of retractions are unique">retractions of retractions</link> are unique.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>14</crumb></trail> <anchor>3574</anchor> <rss>erct-002W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002W</addr>  <route>erct-002W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">embeddings</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002W.agda" type="external">erct-002W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible map</link> <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is an <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">embedding</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 We must show that each <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> is a <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" title="Contractibility">proposition</link>; in fact, each <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" title="Propositions">contractible</link> as <link href="erct-002N.xml" type="local" title="Biinvertible maps are contractible">biinvertible maps are contractible</link>, and <link href="erct-001K.xml" type="local" title="Contractible types are propositions">contractible types are propositions</link>.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>15</crumb></trail> <anchor>3575</anchor> <rss>erct-002X.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002X</addr>  <route>erct-002X.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">Biinvertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" title="Surjection">surjective</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-0029.agda" type="external">erct-0029.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" title="Surjection">surjective</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> This is immediate, using the unit map of <link href="erct-0028.xml" type="local" title="Propositional truncation">propositional truncation</link> and the <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">section</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>16</crumb></trail> <anchor>3576</anchor> <rss>erct-002Y.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-002Y</addr>  <route>erct-002Y.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" title="Surjection">Surjective</link> <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">embeddings</link> are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Y.agda" type="external">erct-002Y.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> that is both <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" title="Surjection">surjective</link> and an <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">embedding</link> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> Fixing <tex>b:B</tex>, we must check that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> of <tex>f</tex> over <tex>b</tex> is <link href="erct-001H.xml" type="local" title="Contractibility">contractible</link>. For the centre of contraction, we must construct an element of this <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link>; because <tex>f</tex> is an <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">embedding</link>, the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is a <link href="erct-001I.xml" type="local" title="Propositions">proposition</link>, so it suffices by the induction principle for <link href="erct-0028.xml" type="local" title="Propositional truncation">propositional truncation</link> to observe that the <link href="erct-001Q.xml" type="local" title="Fiber">fiber</link> is <em>inhabited</em> because <tex>f</tex> is <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" title="Surjection">surjective</link>.</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>17</crumb></trail> <anchor>3577</anchor> <rss>erct-002Z.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002Z</addr>  <route>erct-002Z.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" title="Surjection">Surjective</link> <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">embeddings</link> are <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002Z.agda" type="external">erct-002Z.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A function <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> that is both <link href="erct-0029.xml" type="local" title="Surjection">surjective</link> and an <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">embedding</link> is <link href="erct-000U.xml" type="local" title="Biinverse">biinvertible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 As <link href="erct-002H.xml" type="local" title="Contractible maps are biinvertible">contractible maps are biinvertible</link>, it is enough to recall that <link href="erct-002Y.xml" type="local" title="Surjective embeddings are contractible">surjective embeddings are contractible</link>.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3578</anchor> <rss>erct-001W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001W</addr>  <route>erct-001W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>21</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Coherence for <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" title="Homotopy">homotopies</link> onto the identity</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001W.agda" type="external">erct-001W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>H  \colon  f  \sim   1_{ A }</tex> be a <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" title="Homotopy">homotopy</link> from <tex>f \colon  A  \to  A</tex> onto the identity function. Then we may construct a higher homotopy from <tex>H \circ  f</tex> to <tex>\mathsf {ap}_{ f } \circ  H</tex>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 By the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for functions</link>, we may consider only the case that <tex>f  \equiv   1_{ A }</tex> and <tex>H  \equiv   1_{ 1_{ A } }</tex> exhibit the identity homotopy <tex>1_{ 1_{ 1_{ A } } } \colon   1_{ 1_{ A } }   \sim   1_{ 1_{ A } }</tex>.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3579</anchor> <rss>erct-001V.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>erct-001V</addr>  <route>erct-001V.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>21</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Naturality of <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" title="Homotopy">homotopies</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-001V.agda" type="external">erct-001V.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>H  \colon  f  \sim  g</tex> be a <link href="erct-0014.xml" type="local" title="Homotopy">homotopy</link> between two functions <tex>f,g \colon  A  \to  B</tex>. For any identification <tex>p \colon  x =y</tex> in <tex>A</tex>, we have an identification <tex>H x  \cdot   \mathsf {ap}_{ g } \, p =  \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \, p \cdot  Hy</tex>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 By the <link href="erct-0015.xml" type="local" title="The univalence principle for dependent functions">univalence principle for functions</link>, we may consider just the case that <tex>f  \equiv  g</tex> and <tex>H  \equiv   1_{ f }</tex>, and so we must show that <tex>\mathsf {refl} \cdot   \mathsf {ap}_{ g } p =  \mathsf {ap}_{ f } p \cdot \mathsf {refl}</tex>. By identification induction, we may assume <tex>x \equiv  y</tex> and <tex>p \equiv   \mathsf {refl}</tex> to show <tex>\mathsf {refl} \cdot \mathsf {refl}  =  \mathsf {refl} \cdot \mathsf {refl}</tex>, which is immediate.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3580</anchor> <rss>erct-000W.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000W</addr>  <route>erct-000W.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Inverse</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000W.agda" type="external">erct-000W.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>An <em><strong>inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is defined to be a <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> equipped with an additional higher coherence <tex>\chi   \colon   \mathsf {ap}_{ f } \circ   \eta   \sim   \epsilon \circ  f</tex> in <tex>f \circ  g  \circ  f  \sim  f</tex> relating the (<em>a priori</em> incoherent) unit and the counit of the quasi-inverse.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3581</anchor> <rss>erct-000X.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>erct-000X</addr>  <route>erct-000X.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>19</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Quasi-inverse</title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-000X.agda" type="external">erct-000X.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A <em><strong>quasi-inverse</strong></em> to a function <tex>f  \colon  A  \to  B</tex> is a function <tex>g  \colon  B  \to  A</tex> equipped with homotopies <tex>\epsilon \colon  f  \circ  g  \sim   1_{ B }</tex> and <tex>\eta \colon  g  \circ  f  \sim 1_{ A }</tex>, rendering <tex>g</tex> simultaneously a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">section</link> and a <link href="erct-000Y.xml" type="local" title="Sections and retractions">retraction</link> of <tex>f</tex>.</p><p>Although no coherence laws are assumed for <tex>\eta</tex> and <tex>\epsilon</tex>, we shall refer to them respectively as the <em>unit</em> and <em>counit</em> of the quasi-inverse.</p></mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>3582</anchor> <rss>erct-002M.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>erct-002M</addr>  <route>erct-002M.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>12</month> <day>31</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title><link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">Quasi-invertible</link> maps are <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link></title> <meta name="source">
  
  
  <link href="https://git.sr.ht/~jonsterling/agda-erct/tree/main/item/agda/erct-002M.agda" type="external">erct-002M.agda</link>
</meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-invertible</link> map <tex>f \colon  A \to  B</tex> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.</p>
  
    <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline> 
 Any <link href="erct-000X.xml" type="local" title="Quasi-inverse">quasi-inverse</link> <link href="erct-002C.xml" type="local" title="From quasi-inverses to coherent inverses">can be improved</link> to a <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" title="Inverse">coherent inverse</link>, and <link href="erct-000W.xml" type="local" title="Inverse">any coherently invertible map</link> is <link href="erct-001T.xml" type="local" title="N-truncated map">contractible</link>.
</block>
  
</mainmatter> </tree></backlinks> <references/></backmatter></tree>